Title : Brouwer Medal
Text : {{one source|date=April 2014}}

The '''Brouwer Medal''' is a triennial award presented by the [[Royal Dutch Mathematical Society]] and the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Sciences]]. The Brouwer Metal gets its name from Dutch mathematician, [[L. E. J. Brouwer]] and is The Netherlands’ most prestigious award in mathematics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utwente.nl/ewi/nmc2011/en/brouwer/ |title=The Brouwer Lecture and the Brouwer Medal |publisher=Utwente.nl |date=2014-02-02 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref>

== Recipients ==
*1970 [[René Thom]]
*1973 [[Abraham Robinson]]
*1978 [[Armand Borel]]
*1981 [[Harry Kesten]]
*1984 [[Jürgen Moser]]
*1987 [[Yuri I. Manin]]
*1990 [[W. M. Wonham]]
*1993 [[László Lovász]]
*1996 [[Wolfgang Hackbusch]]
*1999 [[George Lusztig]]
*2002 [[Michael Aizenman]]
*2005 [[Lucien Birgé]]
*2008 [[Phillip Griffiths]]
*2011 [[Kim Plofker]]
*2014  [[John N. Mather]]
*2017 [[Ken Ribet]]

